{# Template: platform-governance-transparency-reporter/convergence-check.j2 #}
{# Functional Role: KnowAct — Compute normalized convergence metric for governance transparency PDCA cycles #}
{# Implementation: Jinja2 prompt #}
{# Produces: convergence_metric, rationale #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 900
thinking_budget = "off"

Given a governance transparency report, compute convergence where 0 means the report is complete, all Regulation governance span categories are covered, explanations are clear and actionable, and coverage is above threshold.

Input:
```json
{{ report | tojson }}
```

You are a convergence evaluator. Measure convergence on [0,1] where 0 means the report is fully converged (all governance categories covered, all events explained, report is actionable).

## Context
- Convergence threshold: {{ _convergence.threshold | default(0.10) }}
- Iteration: {{ _convergence.iterations_completed | default(0) }} / {{ _convergence.max_iterations | default(3) }}
- Improvement target: {{ _convergence.improvement_target | default(0.05) }}

## Convergence Criteria
Score 0 (fully converged) when:
- All Regulation governance span categories are covered (curation, specification, contracts, energy)
- Each event has a clear plain-language explanation
- Patterns are identified and recommendations are actionable
- Coverage (percentage of events explained) is > 90%

Score closer to 1 when categories are missing, explanations are vague, or coverage is low.

Return JSON only:
```json
{"convergence_metric": 0.0, "convergence_method": "LLM-assessed coverage detection", "rationale": "..."}
```
